# https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/cpp/config-mingw

printf("Shows you all the steps necessary")

1. Get the C/C++ extension in the VSC extension tab.
2. Download Mingw-w64:
   2-1. Install MSYS2 -> https://www.msys2.org/
   2-2. On the MSYS prog. execute: "pacman -S --needed base-devel mingw-w64-x86_64-toolchain"
3. Windows+R -> sysdm.cpl -> Advanced -> Edit Environment Variables -> In the upper path add the location of your installed Mingw's bin folder.
4. Check if finished by typing gcc --version in your cmd.
5. Make a new folder and a new file with a .c name
6. Go into Run&Debug tab and make a launch.json file
7. Select g++.exe build and debug in the upper dropdown menu.
8. Good to go :)
